The paper deals with mechanism design and revenue optimization, which are core topics in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also discusses Bayesian Incentive Compatibility and XOS valuations, which are common concepts in algorithmic mechanism design (cs.AI) and computational economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the upper bound on revenue.
